text=:Category: Varia%0a:Essential: {Category.Varia$:essential}%0a:Title: Ethic issues with text generator, GPT3%0a:Author: Simon_Y%0a:Section: A%0a:Completed: 08.05.2021 - 17:40%0a:Status: complete%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a----%0a%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%0a[[#history]]%0a#foxbegin 210511-004618-709730#%0a* [-10.05.2021 - 17:46-] || TA_audrey marked as complete%0a#foxend 210511-004618-709730#%0a[[#historyend]]%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Comments for student'''%0a%0a[[#comments]]%0a%0a[[#commentsend]]%0a%0a----%0a----%0a!!%0a%0aSummary: \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aSome thought on the potential impact GPT-3 might bring%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aGPT-3, or Generative Pre-trained Transformer 3, is an autoregressive language model that uses deep learning to produce human-like text created by OpenAI.%0a%0ahttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GPT-3%0a%0aIt trains on the language data on the internet, and as a result, it is extremely good at producing syntax. The sentence it writes is rarely grammatical. As a result, it is able to generate sentences that are hard to distinguish from a human at first glance. If you would like to see some of the things it wrote, check out this video from Tom Scott.%0a%0ahttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TfVYxnhuEdU%0a%0aIn the video, he asked the engine to write a script for a fake video, and the result is terrifyingly convincing. If you do not fact-check, you would easily be fooled.%0a%0aBut how is this dangerous compared to human spreading misinformation? It is important to remember that if GPT-3 were to be maliciously set up online, it would be capable of spamming fake customer reviews, misleading political arguments, and much more, thousands of times per second. Because these contents generated are much more human-like, it is even more difficult to moderate and identify for the online platform managers. Even worse, the users will have a hard time distinguishing them. Currently, GPT-3’s EULA prohibits such action for a good cause, but these restrictions are hard to reinforce. %0a%0aMuch like the fear that quantum computers will break our current cryptography, the advancement of GPT-3 might just break any anti-bot measures currently deployed. As CMU students who sit at the cutting-edge of technology, we must remind ourselves of the societal impacts of technological advancements. While I am optimistic that GPT-3 issues will be handled, but we must be constantly diligent.%0a%0aRef:%0ahttps://citibeats.com/is-the-gpt-3-ethical-or-not/%0a%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a(:GradedBy: TA_audrey:)
