ven more difficult to moderate and identify for the online platform managers. Even worse, the users will have a hard time distinguishing them. Currently, GPT-3’s EULA prohibits such action for a good cause, but these restrictions are hard to reinforce. %0a%3c %0a%3c Much like the fear that quantum computers will break our current cryptography, the advancement of GPT-3 might just break any anti-bot measures currently deployed. As CMU students who sit at the cutting-edge of technology, we must remind ourselves of the societal impacts of technological advancements. While I am optimistic that GPT-3 issues will be handled, but we must be constantly diligent.%0a%3c %0a%3c Ref:%0a%3c https://citibeats.com/is-the-gpt-3-ethical-or-not/%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
